44
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:32,081
or NPCs, for the player character

45
00:03:32,161 --> 00:03:33,742
to interact with or against.

46
00:03:36,124 --> 00:03:37,745
One of the most crucial decisions

47
00:03:37,885 --> 00:03:41,027
we make as game writers is the question of prescription.

48
00:03:41,668 --> 00:03:45,710
How prescribed versus how open is the player character

49
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:46,231
experience?

50
00:03:48,073 --> 00:03:49,414
So let's look at a spectrum.

51
00:03:49,454 --> 00:03:53,097
On one end, you have Player Avatar from Stardew Valley.

52
00:03:53,537 --> 00:03:57,540
He or she can be molded out of 24 skin tones, 73 hairstyles,

53
00:03:58,081 --> 00:04:01,063
hundreds of combinations of clothing, whatever name you

54
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:04,065
wish, and of course, dog or cat preference.

55
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:07,968
And on the other end of the spectrum, you have Kratos.

56
00:04:09,087 --> 00:04:11,047
Kratos is not an avatar.

57
00:04:11,127 --> 00:04:12,088
Kratos is Kratos.

58
00:04:12,108 --> 00:04:13,568
You do not customize Kratos.

59
00:04:13,748 --> 00:04:15,289
You do not make choices for Kratos.

60
00:04:16,069 --> 00:04:19,211
Kratos' verbs are move, jump, and smash.

61
00:04:21,792 --> 00:04:23,673
So getting a little more nuanced,

62
00:04:24,093 --> 00:04:26,674
here is a character like Max Caulfield

63
00:04:26,914 --> 00:04:28,194
from the original Life is Strange.

64
00:04:29,254 --> 00:04:35,880
Max is obviously a character, she's not an avatar. But as a character, she is designed

65
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:42,826
to be open for how the player wishes to interact with the story. She begins the game shy and

66
00:04:42,866 --> 00:04:48,431
passive. Her relationships are mostly blank slates, giving us a lot of agency to craft them.

67
00:04:49,710 --> 00:04:52,732
And her core objectives align perfectly with the players.

68
00:04:53,393 --> 00:04:55,614
She is seeking to understand the world

69
00:04:55,855 --> 00:04:57,436
and the people around her as we are.

70
00:04:58,016 --> 00:04:59,898
She's confused about her power

71
00:05:00,278 --> 00:05:02,280
and wants to learn more, just like us.

72
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:05,662
And she's undecided about many things,

73
00:05:05,782 --> 00:05:08,024
including her romantic entanglements,

74
00:05:08,525 --> 00:05:09,846
giving us a lot of space

75
00:05:09,866 --> 00:05:11,447
to get to make those choices for her.

76
00:05:13,729 --> 00:05:14,970
Now let's compare that to Chloe

77
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:17,852
